    pearls: ["Staphylococcus aureus causes 70-80% of osteomyelitis cases; always ensure antistaphylococcal coverage in empiric regimen","The sequestrum (dead infected bone) is impenetrable to antibiotics and immune cells -- surgical debridement is mandatory when present on imaging","In sickle cell disease, Salmonella is the most common osteomyelitis pathogen (not S. aureus) due to functional asplenia and gut mucosal ischemia","The OVIVA trial demonstrated that oral antibiotics with high bioavailability (fluoroquinolones, linezolid) are non-inferior to IV therapy after initial IV course for bone and joint infections","Probe-to-bone test in diabetic foot ulcers: if a sterile probe reaches bone through the wound, the PPV for osteomyelitis is approximately 89%","Blood cultures must be obtained BEFORE antibiotics -- a positive blood culture may identify the organism and eliminate the need for invasive bone biopsy","In children, hematogenous osteomyelitis favors the metaphysis of long bones due to sluggish blood flow in sinusoidal veins that allows bacterial seeding"],
