    pearls: ["Anabolic-first, then antiresorptive sequencing produces superior BMD gains compared to starting with bisphosphonate then switching to anabolic","Romosozumab provides the largest 12-month BMD gains of any osteoporosis agent but carries a black box cardiovascular warning -- avoid in patients with recent MI or stroke","Denosumab discontinuation requires mandatory transition to bisphosphonate; rebound bone loss with multiple vertebral fractures can occur within 6-12 months of stopping","Bisphosphonate drug holidays are appropriate after 3-5 years for patients at moderate risk; high-risk patients (T-score ≤-2.5 or prior fracture) should continue therapy","Teriparatide is limited to 2 years of use; starting antiresorptive therapy after anabolic treatment is essential to consolidate bone gains","Osteonecrosis of the jaw risk increases with duration of antiresorptive therapy, dental procedures, and concurrent corticosteroid use -- complete dental work before starting therapy","Atypical femoral fractures present with prodromal thigh pain; if suspected, obtain full-length femur radiographs and discontinue bisphosphonate/denosumab"],
